g Stones' first #1 U.K. hit had a habit of turning up in Bruce's set lists in the strangest places, but fortunately a couple of his team-ups were captured for posterity.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "block_context": {"text": "Cover Me", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/category/cover-me/"}, "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/stones.jpg?fit=1013%2C1024&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200, "srcset": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/stones.jpg?fit=1013%2C1024&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200 1x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/stones.jpg?fit=1013%2C1024&ssl=1&resize=525%2C300 1.5x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/stones.jpg?fit=1013%2C1024&ssl=1&resize=700%2C400 2x"}, "classes": []}, {"id": 18294, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/02/09/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-friends-blowin-down-this-road/", "url_meta": {"origin": 1021, "position": 4}, "title": "Blowin&#8217; Down This Road", "author": "Ken", "date": "February 9, 1987", "format": false, "excerpt": "Woody Guthrie's \"Blowin' Down This Road\" brings Bruce together with his fellow singer-songwriters. Hear him team up with Joe Ely, Joe Grushecky, Elliott Murphy, Alejando Escovedo, and Garland Jeffreys inside.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "block_context": {"text": "Cover Me", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/category/cover-me/"}, "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/admin-ajax-2026-06-08T150851.326.jpg?fit=1000%2C1000&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200, "srcset": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/admin-ajax-2026-06-08T150851.326.jpg?fit=1000%2C1000&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200 1x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/admin-ajax-2026-06-08T150851.326.jpg?fit=1000%2C1000&ssl=1&resize=525%2C300 1.5x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/admin-ajax-2026-06-08T150851.326.jpg?fit=1000%2C1000&ssl=1&resize=700%2C400 2x"}, "classes": []}, {"id": 13795, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/08/23/matr-john-fogerty-and-bruce-springsteen-fortunate-son/", "url_meta": {"origin": 1021, "position": 5}, "title": "Fortunate Son", "author": "Ken", "date": "August 23, 1988", "format": false, "excerpt": "Bruce teamed up with John Fogerty on \"Fortunate Son\" nightly during 2004's Vote for Change Tour, but that wasn't the first time Bruce covered John's anti-war anthem. Listen to rare early bar performances inside.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "block_context": {"text": "Cover Me", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/category/cover-me/"}, "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Fortunate-Son-Main.jpg?fit=1173%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200, "srcset": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Fortunate-Son-Main.jpg?fit=1173%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200 1x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Fortunate-Son-Main.jpg?fit=1173%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=525%2C300 1.5x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Fortunate-Son-Main.jpg?fit=1173%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=700%2C400 2x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Fortunate-Son-Main.jpg?fit=1173%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=1050%2C600 3x"}, "classes": []}], "_links": {"self": [{"href": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/1021", "targetHints": {"allow": ["GET"]}}], "collection": [{"href": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/wp-json/wp/v2/posts"}], "about": [{"href": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/wp-json/wp/v2/types/post"}], "author": [{"embeddable": true, "href": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/wp-json/wp/v2/users/1"